@hkarel you can test it yourself. the running echobot should be exactly this code:
https://github.com/alexbakker/EchoBot
ask on the #toktok channel what toxcore version its linked against (i think Impyy is running it)

> Can you provide a reason for the change in L2541 (return -> continue)?

@sudden6 , you probably meant L2451.
Now how did I come to this: After I added the command PACKET_ID_KEEPALIVE, the amount of ping-pong TCP/UDP incidents dropped dramatically, but it did not disappear at all (as I now understand, it was just a coincidence). Next, I figured out why every 9th second the connection again switches to the UDP.  It turned that at module friend_connection.c has a function send_pings(), which is called on the 9th second. Further, the incident with the "loss" of UDP packets happened on my local network. I thought it was strange: from one point (func. send_pings()) packets always come, from another point (func. send_crypto_packets()) - not always, and this happens on the local network. Next, I assumed that the send_request_packet() function is not always called, and started looking for a reason. The only thing I found was the condition:
```
        if (conn == nullptr) {
            return;
        }
```
Then I wrote a letter to @irungentoo  and asked him why the condition is exactly this. He replied that it is most likely a mistake. I made corrections and started testing. 
By the way, in the code I found at least two more places, where there is the same error.
